\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Previously,
 we learned how to use SPI and I2C to communicate with peripherals.
 This lab we implement the specific knowledge of SPI to communicate with the OLED on top of UART to communicate between peripherals on top of our CC3200 Microcontroller Unit (MCU).
 We also fully learn how to use interrupts to detect rising and falling edges of digital signals.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
We used the Saleae to register the tv signals
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
We used UART to output the decoded version of the signals onto our serial monitors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Combining our ability to communicate with the OLED and decoding TV codes,
 we can combine them into a text message from one Launchpad to another.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In completing this lab,
 we effectively know how to combine both SPI and UART at the same time,
 and get to learn how to both decode and encode basic tv signals running the RC5 protocol 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Background
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Modules,
 hardware,
 and software tools used are as follows.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Modules
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\family typewriter
spi_demo:
 
\family default
Texas Instruments CCS project that demonstrates how to use SPI signals for simple UART communication.
 This module is co-opted and used for all parts of the lab when sending data to the OLED.
 Note this also includes usage for the MCU as both a master & slave:
 we leave just the code for master,
 since that is all that the MCU will be doing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\family typewriter
Adafruit SSD1351 Open Source Graphics Library:
 
\family default
Abridged from the Adafruit graphics library,
 provides an API to write commands (and their subsequent data) to the OLED,
 as well as turn it on.
 Includes various functions to draw complex shapes on the digital display.
 This library is used extensively in this lab & modified.
 More information on the modifications will be detailed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\family typewriter
timer:
 
\family default
Texas Instruments CCS project that shows using the LED's provided by the TI Launchpad how the MCU makes a timer using its built in hardware,
 and is used for the lab to understand a little bit about timing.
 
\end_layout

