\begin_layout Subsection
Decoding IR Transmissions / Application Program
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since they let us to do task 2 to get the decoded signals,
 we decided to skip straight to it in this lab.
 Looking in the datasheets it seems that this is using RC5 protocol,
 which meant multiple things.
 The biggest thing is that it uses a bi-phase coding approach,
 so the goal is to have a program that detects time sections where it detects a transition from high to low or low to high,
 and to have sections between that allow for the transmitter to change the signal before detecting it again.
 We use the rising or falling signals to then figure out the full signal of each button press that is happening.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The way that a packet is transmitted is that it's split into different sections,
 where there is a bit that starts,
 a bit that then changes when a new key is pressed,
 5 bits for the location data,
 then 6 bits for the actual data.
\end_layout

