\begin_layout Standard
Although we were given timer to use,
 at least for this program we decided on using the internal clock of the MCU itself (SysTick),
 and implementing a watchdog around it.
 The timer is forced to fire at every interval,
 but using the MCU's internal clock allows you to start and restart the count at any time.
 When the program starts up/detects every edge,
 it:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Resets SysTick
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Runs SysTick clock down from 0x00FFFFFF (~209ms) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If there's no future signal,
 it sets the timer_counter to 1,
 (this then sends signal to main loop to decode entire signal) 
\end_layout

