\begin_layout Standard
If the code finally detects timer_counter = 1,
 and pulse_idx>0,
 then it calls for decoding the signal,
 to binary,
 and to print out result.
 To deocde,
 we then:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Checks for enough edges to make a RC5 data packet
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Apply noise filtering to only get the valid edge pulses
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Determine if it's a long pulse (1778us) or a short pulse (889us)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Keep a value on half_waiting to find if we are halfway through the bit or not 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If it's a short pulse:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
detect if it's midway through bit
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
if not,
 wait for next part of bit
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
if it is,
 complete the current bit 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
If it's a Long Pulse:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
detect if it's midway through a bit
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
if it isn't,
 then set it to first half
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
if it is,
 then it completes the current bit and starts the next one
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
With the information on whether or not it is high/low from the pulse_buffer,
 we then include that with whether or that was at the mid-point using half_waiting,
 and then prints out 1/0 with the resulting output
\end_layout

